<node id="&quot;CONSTANT-CURRENT INTERVAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Constant-Current Interval is a phase in the charging process where current is maintained at a constant level until a specified voltage is reached."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-95b11f37e6f0ec41fa51536cacde59f4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONSTANT-VOLTAGE INTERVAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Constant-Voltage Interval is a phase in the charging process where the voltage is held constant while the current is adjusted based on the battery's state."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-95b11f37e6f0ec41fa51536cacde59f4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOLTAGE CUTOFF&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
